    {
      "number": 3,
      "title": "副词「再」— The Adverb zài",
      "explanation": "再 (zài) has two key meanings: (1) 'again' for a future repetition — 再说一次 (say it again); (2) 'then/afterwards' in the pattern 先…再… (first…then…). Note: 又 (yòu) is for past repetitions, while 再 is for future or sequential actions.",
      "examples": [
        {
          "chinese": "我先吃饭，再去上班。",
          "pinyin": "Wǒ xiān chī fàn, zài qù shàng bān.",
          "english": "I'll eat first, then go to work."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "请你再说一次。",
          "pinyin": "Qǐng nǐ zài shuō yí cì.",
          "english": "Please say it again."
        }
